  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 00c9c9bb92b3b44fb84ca335c48467d8, type: 3}
  m_Name: Dialogue_Act4_Consult_Bram
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Dialogue.DialogueData
  _id: act4.consult.bram
  _lines:
  - speaker: Wren
    text: Bram. Lord Aldric has made an offer. I would hear what you think of it.
    isCloseup: 0
    voiceClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 5f3e724dc4d574a1a8d63506c7c9a036, type: 3}
  - speaker: Bram
    text: A lord's banner over the door would bring the road back. Traders, coin,
      a full common room by winter.
    isCloseup: 1
    voiceClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 6c88b3bbce71a434daaad3cef35280d0, type: 3}
  - speaker: Bram
    text: But a road that comes because a lord allows it can be closed the same way.
      I have poured for men who owned the roof they drank under. They did not laugh
      the same.
    isCloseup: 1
    voiceClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 15d1a5ace30c7439ca79e3afcd2ab6e7, type: 3}
